Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of diversity measures in network-structured data, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on heterogeneous information networks (HINs) suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of diversity measures in information retrieval and recommender systems suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The discussion of social media studies and the use of network analysis suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
